//==============================================================================//Name://  MaterialRenamer.mel//==============================================================================//Purpose://  Переименование материала по имени текстуры.//==============================================================================//Usage://  1. Save the MaterialRenamer.mel to your scripts directory.//  2. Start Maya. In the command line type MaterialRenamer();//  3. Middlemouse drag to a shelf you like.//==============================================================================//        SCRIPT NAME:  MaterialRenamer.mel v2.0 (Maya4 version)//        AUTHOR:  Thomas Hamilton//        LAST UPDATED:   October 20, 2003//        www.thomashamilton.homestead.com//DESCRIPTION://MaterialRenamer searches through all of your material balls, and then checks to see what file//is attached to it, and also if (and how much) it is tiled(within the material attributes).//It then renames the file node to the name of the image file used, and the material ball correctly//based on it's tiling amount.  A material using the texture Metal04.tga and not being tiled would//be renamed to Metal04_M,if it was tiled 3 in U, and 2 in V, it would be renamed Metal04_32T.//NAMING CONVENTION BREAKDOWN://Material Ball=        Filename_M//Tiled MaterialBall=        Filename_##T//Suface Shader=        Filename_S//File Node=                Filename_extention//MaterialInfo=         FileName_MatInfo//SETUP://To load, type MaterialRenamer in the command line, highlight, and middle mouse drag to//your shelf.global proc MaterialRenamer(){	python("import MaterialRenamer; MaterialRenamer.MaterialRenamer()");}